7:
Where'd I put my grocery list...
Let's see, food, potions, what else...
15:
Whoops, sorry 'bout that, kiddo!
You all right?
18:
Yup, I'm okay! I shouldn't have been
spacing out in the middle of the street.
21:
I wasn't looking where I was going
either. I'm in a hurry, so I'll have to dash,
but glad you're okay!
26: Oh, you were looking, all right.
30: But unluckily for you, so was I.
34: Cough up what you stole, pickpocket.
48:
If he's got the guts to pull a stunt like
that in broad daylight, he should go
earn himself an honest living in the
Kaleidoscope.
50:
Well... Doubt he'd last long, even in the
shallows.
54: Um, thank you for the help!
58:
No worries. Name's Conner. I work as an
adventurer 'round these parts.
61: I'm Alk. I'm also an adventurer... Kind of.
64:
It's a bit embarrassing to call myself an
adventurer after what just happened...
68:
Yeah, well, you know the saying.
"Fool me once, shame on you. Fool me
twice, shame on me." Experience counts.
Now you know better.
70:
With the Guild's greedy thugs running
things, it's hardly surprising the city's
a rough place.
72: But hey, kinda suits a lowlife like me.
76:
Lowlife? You don't look like a bad person
to me, though.
79:
Looks can be surprising. You might not
wanna go trusting every guy who does
you a tiny favor.
83:
I dunno, I've met a lot of odd people,
so I'd say I'm a pretty good judge of
character by now!
87:
You're an odd one, yourself.
I'd best get going, though. Seeya, kid.
92:
Wait! Um, could I maybe take you out to
lunch? I'd like to repay you for the help!
97:
Whew. Never been on a date with a guy,
but there's a first time for everything,
I guess.
104:
I guess you could call me that.
Honestly, I'm just a run-of-the-mill
adventurer.
106:
I take on Guild quests and hope I find
the odd treasure or two along the way.
Nothin' special.
108:
Sometimes I join parties, sometimes
I just do my own thing.
112:
You can take on the Kaleidoscope by
yourself? That's so cool!
115:
...What, you want me to take you in
with me? I can see it written all over
your face.
119:
You can? You're really observant!
Catching pickpockets, reading people's
expressionsno wonder you make
a great adventurer!
122: I dunno about the "great" part, kid.
124:
Besides, you've already got your own
party to adventure with, haven't you?
128: I mean, I guess I do, but...
130:
I want to get strongerstrong enough
that people are relying on ME, instead
of me always relying on them.
132:
Remember what you told me earlier?
About how experience counts?
134:
If I want to learn how to rely on my own
strength, I need experience adventuring
without my party, right?
138:
Sigh All right, but just the shallows.
Meet me back here with your weapon of
choice and at least three days' rations.
146:
Lesson number one: never a bad idea to
build your network.
149:
Thank you so much, Conner! I was right,
you really ARE a good guy!
